<p>I use <code>echo</code> inside a function to display a single value on webpage but I also can do it in another way use <code>return</code> function. </p>  <p>Which way is better? I want my code to be reuse-able and tight.   </p>  <p>Option 1 <code>echo</code>: </p>  <pre><code>function display_wuuk_time($link, $taskid){//      $sql = "SELECT start from wuuk where id =$taskid;";     $result = mysql_query($sql, $link);      $datetime = mysql_result($result,0);     echo "&lt;b&gt;$datatme&lt;/b&gt;";  }; </code></pre>  <p>Option 2 <code>return</code>: </p>  <pre><code>function return_wuuk_time($link, $taskid){//      $sql = "SELECT start from wuuk where id =$taskid;";     $result = mysql_query($sql, $link);      $isempty = mysql_num_rows($result);     If($isempty ==0){return 0;}//if no rating       $datetime = mysql_result($result,0);     return $datetime;  }; </code></pre>  <p>display.html:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php // Option 1 display_wuuk_time($link, $taskid);  // Option 2  $datetime = return_wuuk_time($link, $taskid); echo &lt;b&gt;$datetime&lt;/b&gt; ?&gt; </code></pre>